Title: 'Lalibela '
DateModified: '2019-03-04'
DatePublished: '2019-03-04'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/lalibela
SetInCountry: Ethiopia
Category: Making a local connection
AuthorName: Giovanna Catussi
AuthorCountry: Canada
Text: A social worker from The United States, travel to Ethiopia with the purpose
  of finding solutions for the huger which unfortunately haunst Ethiopia. She falls
  in love with the country, its people and culture. She discovers that the real happiness
  is simply there. She learns how to feed herself using hands and suddenly her life
  in Chicago does not make sense anymore, on her memories, she remembers her marriage
  and years of arguments with her husband who does not understand her need to help
  the world. Suddenly, she meets Philip, a soldier from England, and they have a romantic
  story based on the pleasure of helping people and a meaningful life. They adopts
  two childs who were in a local hospital struggling for their lives.
